why do people cry you cry when your sad and happy sometimes too but why it's not like the tears do anything so what could the reason be i think that sometimes it's the only non destructive way that your body can release emotion okay so i cry at sad movies not all of them sometimes they just pull at your heartstrings i can count on one hand the times i have cried because i was happy the time my father pulled out of his second quadruple bypass surgery for instance it was joy and relief the day i got married tears roll down my face when i am so mad that constuctive words just won't come out of my mouth when all i want to do is swear and fight back and i can't although embarrassed because people associate tears with weakness i would rather have them roll than suffer the consequences of my own anger no matter what the circumstances behind tears i feel a sense of relief afterwards Tears for Fears Tears Miss Saigon Marie Antoinette Emotion Trish Stratus Shaggy dog story Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The Amber Spyglass YuYu Hakusho Mojave people Pitaten Johnny Cash John the Baptist Empathy Knots Landing Shinn Asuka Scenes from a Memory Night (book) Piccolo Junior Saga Happiness Clinical depression Mobile Fighter G Gundam Traumatic brain injury Jon Secada Gundam W G-Unit: Last Outpost Utilitarianism Noel Gallagher Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Aphasia Vegeta Super Princess Peach Force (Star Wars) Teen Girl Squad Bernard Williams Suicide Kate Bush 50 First Dates Kodocha Liam Gallagher Muslim ibn Aqeel Episodes of Lost (Season 1) One Tree Hill (TV series) Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Son Gohan Breastfeeding The Beatles discography The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (film) Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Transsexuality Bhajan The Good Soldier Dead Like Me Goodness and value theory One Piece minor characters Darth Vader EastEnders The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Jam (TV series) Prostate cancer Time Out of Mind Melanie Wilkes Sting (musician) Nine